# 1. Create three classes Calculator, SCCalculator and HybridCalculator and group them into a package.

## Code

### Calculator.java

```java id="8v2mql"
package mypackage;

public class Calculator {

    public int add(int a, int b) {

        return a + b;
    }
}
```

---

### SCCalculator.java

```java id="4v8qwr"
package mypackage;

public class SCCalculator {

    public double square(int n) {

        return n * n;
    }
}
```

---

### HybridCalculator.java

```java id="9m1qvl"
package mypackage;

public class HybridCalculator extends Calculator {

    public int multiply(int a, int b) {

        return a * b;
    }
}
```

---

### Main.java

```java id="2p7mzk"
import mypackage.*;

class Main {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Calculator c = new Calculator();

        System.out.println("Addition = " + c.add(10, 5));

        SCCalculator s = new SCCalculator();

        System.out.println("Square = " + s.square(4));

        HybridCalculator h = new HybridCalculator();

        System.out.println("Multiplication = " + h.multiply(3, 4));
    }
}
```

---

## Output

```text id="6n2qpk"
